<Base title="SocialProof for Martial Arts Schools — Student Testimonials That Fill Classes | SocialProof" description="Martial arts schools: collect student and parent testimonials to fill classes and build community trust. Show real results, not just belt photos.">
  <main>
    <section style="max-width:860px;margin:0 auto;padding:3rem 1.5rem;">
      <h1 style="font-size:2.5rem;font-weight:800;line-height:1.2;margin-bottom:1rem;">
        Social Proof for Martial Arts Schools
      </h1>
      <p style="font-size:1.2rem;color:#555;margin-bottom:2rem;">
        Parents choosing a martial arts school for their child are making a values decision as much as a fitness one. They want evidence of discipline, safety, instructor quality, and community. Student and parent testimonials answer those questions better than any brochure.
      </p>

      <h2 style="font-size:1.6rem;font-weight:700;margin-top:2.5rem;">What prospective students and parents want to hear</h2>
      <p>They want to hear from people like them — parents of shy kids who found confidence, adults who started at 40, teenagers who needed focus and found it. Real testimonials from real students in your dojo carry more weight than instructor credentials alone.</p>

      <h2 style="font-size:1.6rem;font-weight:700;margin-top:2.5rem;">Testimonials that resonate for martial arts enrollment</h2>
      <ul style="padding-left:1.5rem;line-height:1.9;">
        <li><strong>Transformation stories:</strong> "My son was getting bullied. Six months in, he carries himself differently. Totally different kid."</li>
        <li><strong>Adult beginners:</strong> "Started at 42 with zero experience. Instructors are patient and the community is welcoming to newcomers."</li>
        <li><strong>Parent peace of mind:</strong> "They take safety seriously. Every class is supervised and the instructors know every student by name."</li>
        <li><strong>Focus and discipline:</strong> "My daughter's grades improved after she started training. The discipline carries over into everything."</li>
        <li><strong>Community feel:</strong> "It's not a gym. It's a family. We've made lifelong friends here."</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 style="font-size:1.6rem;font-weight:700;margin-top:2.5rem;">How to collect testimonials at your dojo</h2>
      <p>The best time to ask is at belt promotions, after a student's first competition, or when a parent mentions how much their child has grown. Send your SocialProof collection link via text message — most parents respond within minutes when you catch them at an emotional high. Display the widget on your homepage, class schedule page, and free trial signup page.</p>

